Part 1: Data

  • Rrandomly sampled movies released before 2016. -we cannot perform causation since it can only be inferred from a randomized experiment.(and no expermint here). - associations. cant be infered since observational studies are generally only used to show associations. - only correlations can be infered and since the sampling is random the results are generalisable to the bigger population * * *

Part 2: Research question

Response variable: explantory variables :

does best_pic_nom ,best_pic_win best_actor_win,best_actress_win, best_dir_win, top200_box affected (have influence on) audience_score

Part 5: Prediction

predict movie score where best_pic_nom =0 nd best_dir_win=0 and top200_box=0 also preict when best_pic_nom =1 nd best_dir_win=1 and top200_box=1 and best_pic_nom =1 nd best_dir_win=0 and top200_box=1

newscore <- data.frame(best_pic_nom = 0, best_dir_win = 0, top200_box=0)
predict(ml, newscore)
